The sum of the 8 neighbors of **2026** is **16156**.

This spiral starts at 1 in the center, moving right to 2, down to 3, left to 4-5, up to 6-7, right to 8-9, and continues outward in layers[2]. The position of 2026 is found using the standard number spiral formula: compute the layer \( l = \lceil \sqrt{2026} \rceil = 45 \) (since \( 44^2 = 1936 \) and \( 45^2 = 2025 \)), then since \( 2026 = 2025 + 1 \), it is at row 22 (0-indexed), column 23[2].

The 8 neighbor positions (row \( r \), column \( c \)) and their values are:

| Position | Coordinates | Value |
